comments: Carter Jr. (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Jackson's (DET) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bey (DET) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by LaVine (CHI).
LaVine (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position on Grant (DET) during the screen and absorbs the contact.
LaVine (CHI) jumps alongside Grant (DET) to legally contest his jump shot attempt.
Carter Jr. (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Wright's (DET) path and absorbs the contact.
Wright (DET) makes contact with Carter Jr.'s (CHI) head that affects his driving shot attempt.
Carter Jr. (CHI) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position as he absorbs the body contact during Grant's (DET) driving shot attempt.
LaVine (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position on Grant (DET) following the screen, and the contact is marginal.
Carter Jr. (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Grant (DET) and any "high-five" contact after the release is deemed incidental.
Jackson (DET) makes clean ball contact as he tries to deflect the pass away from LaVine (CHI) and any follow-through body contact during the steal attempt is deemed incidental.
Carter Jr. (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact during Plumlee's (DET) shot attempt near the basket.
White (CHI) places two resting hands to Smith Jr.'s (DET) back while Smith Jr. and LaVine (CHI) engage and disengage, and the contact is marginal.
Ellington (DET) commits a take foul on White (CHI).
Plumlee (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in LaVine's (CHI) path and absorbs the contact as he goes under the screen.
Plumlee (DET) grabs and pulls Carter Jr.'s (CHI) arm and the contact dislodges him from his rebounding position.
White (CHI) makes contact with Bey's (DET) arm that affects his shot near the rim.
Plumlee (DET) commits a take foul on LaVine (CHI).
Temple (CHI) and Ellington (DET) engage and disengage during the screen, and the contact is marginal.
Satoransky (CHI) legally contests Wright's (DET) jump shot attempt.
